div.p: The CLI tool, web interface, or the Repeater module can request the Main module to send an encrypted message to a certain ship.
- Get the ships symmetric key from the database module using the ships ID.
- Pass the key and the plain text message to the encryption module
- Send a composed message with an unique message ID, the ships ID and the message itself to the send module
- The send module splits the composed message in packets to send to BP
- Receive module received the message, adds the signal strength to it, and puts it in a folder (or DB)
- Main module on ship reads the folder
- Decrypt the message with the encryption module by trying all the keys in the Database module
- Put the message ID, signal strength and the decrypted message in a file in a folder
- Subproject Half-duplex reads the folder and sends an acknowledgement and signal strength back
